  I have completed the review of the codebase following the rename from
  'Phalanx' to 'Runsight'. My findings indicate that the source code and
  documentation have been successfully updated, but several infrastructure and
  configuration items remain.


  Summary of Findings

  • Source Code: libs/core and apps/api have been renamed to runsight_core
    and runsight_api respectively. Imports have been updated accordingly.
  • Documentation: All Markdown files in .agora/ and the root README.md and
    AGENTS.md have been updated.
  • GUI: apps/gui has been updated, including package.json and internal logo
    references.



  Issues Identified

  1. CI Configuration: .github/workflows/ci.yml still references the phalanx/
      directory, which will break CI.
  2. Database Files: phalanx.db and state.db in the root remain and should be
      migrated to runsight.db and runsight_state.db.
  3. Infrastructure Directory: The .phalanx/ directory still exists and has
     not been migrated to .runsight/.
  4. IDE Rules: .cursor/rules/phalanx.mdc still exists and should be renamed
     to runsight.mdc.
  5. Git Configuration: .gitignore still references .phalanx/ and
     phalanx.mdc.
  6. Workspace Config: Root pyproject.toml still references apps/cli/tests,
     even though the CLI application has been dropped.
  7. CLI Tool: The system CLI command remains phalanx and has not been
     updated to runsight.

  I have posted a summary of these findings to the team feed and written the
  final artifact to
  .phalanx/teams/team-bdacc51d/agents/reviewer-8e2c537b/artifact.json.
